title: Game Client wont Launch
body:
For about the 4th time I've uninstalled and re-installed League and it hasnt helped anything.. so i've finally decided to come here for help.

The other week Im not sure why, but League just wouldnt Launch. 

Rundown of what happens..

1. Open the League Launcher 
2. Click the Orange "LAUNCH" Button
3. Hear the sound it makes when you click it usually but no Disclaimer comes up/nothing happens
4. 20-30 seconds later disclaimer comes up and then well.. nothing happens when I hit accept.


Other things ---- 
When I click anything within the Launcher, for example Repair. Nothing happens either, the repair Accept/Decline box doesnt show up.

replies.body: man i am getting the exact same thing, it is super frustrating as i've tried everything recommended and even possible solutions posted by others.  Normally i can go ahead and troubleshoot many lol issues myself or just wait it out till rito fixes it. However i am completely stumped this time around as i come back from overseas to the new patch and this shit happens now. Wot fkn DO????

I would like to put in here that I have finally found a fix to this (worked for me anyway).  I completely uninstalled my Anti-Virus software (BitDefender).  This, along with a restart made it work.  I then reinstalled my anti-virus.  Once I knew that was the problem, I went through not just the 'Firewall' part of the software, but EVERYTHING and methodically added League of Legends files to all the exclusion lists I could find.   Hope this helps others.
Has anyone found a fix for this yet?  Have this same problem myself.  Windows 10 X64
No fix for this yet, someone please help?

I'm getting the exact same issue yet haven't really seen many people post about it.

Not using windows 10 or anything. Still using windows 8.1.

This hasn't even been posted on reddit once which is usually what it takes for something to be fixed.
